The '''Taloron Hunters''' were a group of elite [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] and hunters who operated in [[Wild Space/Legends|Wild Space]] after the demise of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. The [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Crutag]] was one such hunter.

Their [[Taloron Hunter armor|standard attire]] included protective [[Armor/Legends|armor]] over padding, including a skirt to protect the upper legs, a wide-brimmed helmet, a [[Backpack/Legends|backpack]], a side pouch, a [[Blaster carbine/Legends|blaster carbine]] with affixed [[Vibroblade/Legends|vibrobayonet]], and a non-powered [[Sword/Legends|sword]].

The Taloron Hunters designed and manufactured the [[Taloron Prey Chaser|Prey Chaser]].

==Behind the scenes==
The Taloron Hunter illustration in ''[[The Star Wars Sourcebook]]'' is taken from concept art for [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']] which eventually evolved into the [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Emperor's Royal Guards]]. The same illustration later inspired the [[Imperial Sentinel]]s of ''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire]]'', as well as the cancelled [[Kenner Products|Kenner]] [[action figure]] [[Atha Prime/Legends|Atha Prime]]. There are also many similarities between their appearance and that of [[Embo/Legends|Embo]].

